(xiii) framtida (8), 
(xiv) Djurgårdsstaden (13), 
(xv) Hjorthagen (10)

Total long words (B) = 15 

Since (B) denotes number of long words and we also have an additional measure for single 'long words' requirement in LIX the proportion of long words per total is (B/A).

Average number of long words per sentence (B/A) = 15/41 = 0.365
 

3. LIX readability score =  LIX = A x S + 100 x B 
   = (  ( 41/ 41 ) x ( 41/ 3 ) ) x ( (1-( 15/41))  ) + 100 x (15/41)
   = (1 x 13.67) x (1-0.365) +100 x (0.365)
   but here applied through a simpler LIX calculation 
   = S + (  B/ total words  )  x 100 
   = 13.67 +  ( 0.365  ) x 100 
   
 LIX=64.02